<paragraph blockId="22.[151,757,942,968]" box="[151,757,942,968]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,757,942,968]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
3. 
<taxonomicName authority="BURMEISTER, 1838" authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[181,757,942,968]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropterinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">PHANEROPTERINAE BURMEISTER, 1838</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1014,1221]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
This is the most speciose subfamily of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krauss" authorityYear="1902" box="[578,728,1014,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tettigoniidae</taxonomicName>
, comprehending 2,803 described species distributed in 379 genera and 34 tribes (
<bibRefCitation author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[354,584,1050,1076]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refId="ref30789" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2022) Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // orthoptera. speciesfile. org (accessed 13 March 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Cigliano 
<emphasis box="[459,516,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
). From this total, 294 species belonging to 66 genera are currently recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[194,262,1086,1112]" name="Brazil" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and, regarding the 
<collectingRegion box="[494,640,1086,1112]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
, a single species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rehn, 1950" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[853,1235,1086,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Machima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paranensis">
<emphasis box="[853,1092,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Machima paranensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rehn, J. A. G." box="[1103,1235,1086,1113]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="271 - 319" refId="ref35633" refString="Rehn, J. A. G. (1950) Studies in the Group Dysoniae (Aphidniae of authors) (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Phaneropterinae) Part I. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 75 (3 - 4), 271 - 319." type="journal article" year="1950">Rehn, 1950</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[1254,1370,1086,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dysoniini">Dysoniini</taxonomicName>
), was recorded so far. Here we present the first records of 56 species, seven tribes (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[1014,1173,1122,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Microcentrini">Microcentrini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[1184,1310,1122,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Odonturini">Odonturini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Phaneropterini">Phaneropterini</taxonomicName>
, Phyllopterini, Pycnopalpini, Scudderiini and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Emsley &amp; Nickle" authorityYear="1969" box="[737,885,1158,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Steirodontini">Steirodontini</taxonomicName>
) and three genus groups (Aniarae, Cosmophylla and Scaphurae) for the state.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
